saying: The dog wags his tail, not for you, but for your bread.
description: Walker is a lazy dog villager in the Animal Crossing series who first appeared in Doubutsu no Mori e+ as one of six starter cards bundled with the game, alongside Maggie, Rod, Merry, Angus, and Willow, respectively. His name relates to walks, or walking, which dogs are known to enjoy. His initial phrase, "wuh," relates to his personality type, which means "what" in a dazed expression. His Japanese catchphrase is shared with Bow, another lazy dog villager that appears in Doubutsu no Mori e+. He is also the only dog from Doubutsu no Mori e+ to ever return in another Animal Crossing series game.
